<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="266" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="15.[811,1457,1459,1900]" box="[813,903,1459,1485]" pageId="15" pageNumber="266">REMARK</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[811,1457,1459,1900]" pageId="15" pageNumber="266">
Only 
<specimenCount box="[875,1022,1491,1517]" pageId="15" pageNumber="266" type="generic">one specimen</specimenCount>
of this savanna species was captured at a thicket edge in Kalakpa Resource Reserve, a mostly savannacovered legally-protected area in the south of the Volta Region, southeast of the Abutia Hills. 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Ogilby" baseAuthorityYear="1835" box="[1126,1383,1586,1612]" class="Mammalia" family="Pteropodidae" genus="Epomophorus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="266" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="gambianus">
<emphasis box="[1126,1383,1586,1612]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="266">Epomophorus gambianus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is well documented from Eastern Ghana and 
<collectingCountry box="[1214,1269,1619,1645]" name="Togo" pageId="15" pageNumber="266">Togo</collectingCountry>
and is most common in savanna or secondary savanna areas. During three Belgian expeditions to 
<collectingCountry box="[1072,1131,1683,1709]" name="Togo" pageId="15" pageNumber="266">Togo</collectingCountry>
, including many localities in the 
<collectingCountry box="[855,910,1715,1741]" name="Togo" pageId="15" pageNumber="266">Togo</collectingCountry>
Highlands, it was the second most abundant fruit bat after 
<taxonomicName authority="(Peters, 1868)" baseAuthorityName="Peters" baseAuthorityYear="1868" box="[910,1299,1746,1773]" class="Mammalia" family="Pteropodidae" genus="Micropteropus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="266" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pusillus">
<emphasis box="[910,1141,1746,1772]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="266">Micropteropus pusillus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="PETERS W." box="[1155,1291,1746,1773]" pageId="15" pageNumber="266" pagination="865 - 872" refId="ref22060" refString="PETERS W. 1868. - Fortsetzung und der Schluss einer Ubersicht der Flederhunde. Monatsberichte der Koniglich-Preussischen Akademie der Wissenschaften zu Berlin 1868: 865 - 872." type="journal article" year="1868">Peters, 1868</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
(DeVree 
<emphasis box="[1404,1456,1746,1772]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="266">et al.</emphasis>
1969; 1970; 
<bibRefCitation author="DE VREE F. &amp; VAN DER STRAETEN E." box="[950,1308,1778,1804]" pageId="15" pageNumber="266" pagination="159 - 164" refId="ref17980" refString="DE VREE F. &amp; VAN DER STRAETEN E. 1971. - Contribution a l'etude des chiropteres de la Republique duTogo. 3. Liste preliminaire des Chiropteres recoltes par la troisieme Mission zoologique belge au Togo. R evue de Zoologie et de Botanique Africaines 83: 159 - 164." type="journal article" year="1971">De Vree &amp; Van der Straeten 1971</bibRefCitation>
). In the Volta Region 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Ogilby" baseAuthorityYear="1835" box="[892,1029,1810,1836]" class="Mammalia" family="Pteropodidae" genus="Epomophorus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="266" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="gambianus">
<emphasis box="[892,1029,1810,1836]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="266">E. gambianus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was previously recorded from Bator, Ho, Keta, Kete Krachi (= Kradji), and Odomi Jongo, 
<quantity box="[1350,1428,1841,1868]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.218688" pageId="15" pageNumber="266" unit="mi" value="2.0">2 miles</quantity>
E Nkwanta (
<bibRefCitation author="BERGMANS W." box="[928,1098,1874,1900]" pageId="15" pageNumber="266" pagination="75 - 146" refId="ref16897" refString="BERGMANS W. 1988. - Taxonomy and biogeography of African fruit bats (Mammalia, Megachiroptera). 1. General Introduction; material and methods; results: The genus Epomophorus Bennett, 1836. Beaufortia 38: 75 - 146." type="journal article" year="1988">Bergmans 1988</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="266" type="conservation">
<paragraph blockId="15.[811,1455,1923,2026]" pageId="15" pageNumber="266">
CONSERVATION STATUS. — 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Ogilby" baseAuthorityYear="1835" box="[1069,1296,1923,1947]" class="Mammalia" family="Pteropodidae" genus="Epomophorus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="266" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="gambianus">
<emphasis box="[1069,1296,1923,1947]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="266">Epomophorus gambianus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is listed as “Least Concern” on the IUCN Red List. Although rare during our survey, the high abundance of this fruit bat in surveys that included savanna areas make it a species of less concern.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
